Hancock Foods conducted a prevention program compliance audit in conjunction with the 5-year revision and resubmittal of its Risk Management Plan.  Several findings were identified as a result of this compliance audit.  The following items were identified as a result of the audit and will be addressed by Hancock Foods by 12/31/2009:

-  Preparation of revised piping and instrumentation drawings for each covered process;
-  Preparation of a revised maximum intended inventory quantity for each of the three refrigeration systems;
-  Preparation of a revised and updated process hazard analysis (PHA);
-  Review and revision of operating procedures for each refrigeration system and certification that these operating procedures are current and accurate;
-  Preparation of revised training course curriculum, completion of refresher training for each employee who operates or maintains the refrigeration systems, and documentation of training for each employee;
-  Performance of a mechanical integrity inspection for each of the three ammonia refrigeration systems, to include written documentation of each inspection and test procedure; and
-  Preparation of a revised written employee participcation plan.

